00:01:11.180 --> 00:01:15.660
so my props might be getting
a little bit shabby inside.

00:01:15.660 --> 00:01:19.560
So I thought I would try
to use a few props to get

00:01:19.560 --> 00:01:22.290
you thinking about
the sociological

00:01:22.290 --> 00:01:24.750
meaning of connection.

00:01:24.750 --> 00:01:26.850
And really, connection
is at the core

00:01:26.850 --> 00:01:28.120
of what it is to be a human.

00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:30.450
And that's what
sociologists look at.

00:01:30.450 --> 00:01:32.340
We look at how
people are, how they

00:01:32.340 --> 00:01:35.450
experience the world in
terms of their connectedness

00:01:35.450 --> 00:01:36.914
with others.

00:01:36.914 --> 00:01:39.330
And that's really important
because to connect with others

00:01:39.330 --> 00:01:42.270
takes you out of
the privatized self.

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:46.470
And it creates, then, for us,
a public realm in which people

00:01:46.470 --> 00:01:50.580
can interconnect.

00:01:50.580 --> 00:01:52.410
And I suppose what
I'm trying to argue

00:01:52.410 --> 00:01:54.870
is that there is a
continued significance

00:01:54.870 --> 00:01:57.780
to that connectedness
in the digital age.

00:01:57.780 --> 00:02:01.530
And I'm arguing, really,
in a sense, for a material

00:02:01.530 --> 00:02:03.190
understanding of connectedness.

00:02:03.190 --> 00:02:05.970
So what I'm going to talk to
you about is connectedness

00:02:05.970 --> 00:02:08.759
or connectivity, not in
terms of the digital sphere,

00:02:08.759 --> 00:02:13.000
which is where you guys all
work and excel, but in real,

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:17.640
grounded, rooted, co-present
kind of connectivity,

00:02:17.640 --> 00:02:20.430
which has been central to the
work that I've been doing over

00:02:20.430 --> 00:02:21.250
the last--

00:02:21.250 --> 00:02:24.910
I don't even want to say it--
three decades as a sociologist.

00:02:24.910 --> 00:02:28.500
So I'm not going to talk
about the Internet of Things.

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:31.620
I'm going to talk about
the sociology of things.

00:02:31.620 --> 00:02:34.440
And if I have time, I'll try and
move on and talk a little bit

00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:36.510
about disconnect because
there's another side

00:02:36.510 --> 00:02:39.030
to this whole
connection narrative.

00:02:39.030 --> 00:02:41.550
But we might leave that
